\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is through these imperfect networks that the idea of a social capital
 comes about.
 These are powers exercised by the participants where formal lending doesn't
 exist.
 These are difficult to measure but indeed matter in a traditional society.
 Note that social capital doesn't always work in favour of insurance.
 It might in fact be impossible to provide insurance because they go against
 the established social norms or group identities.
 
